Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Executive Summary TAZA Corp. was conceived during the initial stages of the real estate market crash in 2008 to address the lifecycle of acquiring, marketing, and selling distressed real estate properties and assets. During the first two years, TAZA achieved over $1Mil in sales revenue, and currently services over 120,000 registered users. TAZA utilizes the best of class in technology and vendors, with established relationships with Microsoft, Apple, Google, and Rackspace, offering TAZA immediate access to world-class resources. The stream of resources include astounding engineering skills, software, hardware, database systems, development facilities, Microsoft Azure Cloud full diversity, mobile development and integration on all smart devices, and lifetime clients who are interested in innovations and client-oriented services. The hierarchy of resources allows TAZA to become one of the most innovative and resourceful software company in the industry. TAZA is able to take full advantage of market opportunities on immediate basis to address new areas in the existing market segment and similar business solutions in new markets.  Extended and new market segments include Customer Relationship Management (CRM), Manufacturing Resource Planning (MRP), Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP), and Loan Servicing and Initiation. TAZA brought many innovations to the real estate distressed market that are key components to any new market segments. Process and progress transparency is the main ingredient used in all TAZA systems and components; in certain cases this transparency includes emails and journaling content. Mobile innovations have set TAZA apart from all the competition as the mobile workforce is fully integrated in real-time with the entire chain of production and distribution.  TAZA produces and supports all of its products locally in the US. Business analysis, software development, market testing, client services, training and support are all based locally in San Diego, CA, and Boise ID. With this in-sourced business strategy, TAZA has been able to stay very close to the clients and to the market, and to immediately anticipate and react with superior quality solutions to the continually changing market needs. TAZA has become a business software platform that is able to address complex financial and industrial markets.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: THB Intermediaries, LLC is a national boutique brokerage specializing in the placement of facultative property and casualty reinsurance and program administration. Since its creation in 1984, THB has been a recognized leader in this specialized market segment operating through its strategically located offices in New York, Hartford, Atlanta, Chicago, Dallas and Los Angeles. Facultative brokers are "risk specialists", placing the most difficult account exposures such as windstorm, flood and earthquake in the property sector and workers' compensation, general liability and auto liability in the casualty sector. THB Intermediaries is fundamentally different from other brokerages. Unlike our facultative competitors who serve as mere service centers for a larger treaty operation, THB Intermediaries was conceived and operates as a true stand-alone facultative specialist. Also unlike many of our competitors who function primarily as conduits on business generated by their retail parent, THB produces its own business directly from a diverse, national client base of insurance carriers, retail and wholesale brokers and managing general agents and administers all accounting and claims through our proprietary facultative software known as "Profac". Profac provides a seamless integration of placement, accounting and claims documentation that ensures a measure of speed and accuracy that is without peer in facultative brokerage.

Full Description: n 1969, two young trial lawyers from Port Arthur, Texas, started a law firm that has since become legendary in Texas and built a nationwide reputation for helping individuals recover compensation for injuries. The son of a constable (David Provost, now deceased) and the son of a justice of the peace (Walter Umphrey) started a tradition of helping individuals get the justice they need and deserve. "We balance justice for the working man. Someone has to do it, and that's my business." – Walter Umphrey, recognized in 2010 by Texas Lawyer magazine as one of the 25 greatest Texas lawyers of the past quarter century Fighting for the Legal Rights of Individuals and Families Since 1969 The Provost Umphrey Law Firm's principal office is a renovated fruit warehouse in Beaumont, Texas. Saved from the wrecking ball, our 1923 building is the nerve center for more than 20 attorneys and 100 staff members. We focus all our firm's resources on obtaining justice for individuals harmed by negligence – building each case for victory in a jury trial if necessary to attain justice for our client. Our clients include: People who have suffered personal injury or a wrongful death in the family under a broad range of circumstances Victims of dangerous drugs and medical products who need to pursue pharmaceutical or medical device litigation – as well as others with valid products liability claims Drivers and passengers hurt in motor vehicle and aviation accidents People injured on the job in construction, maritime, manufacturing, railroad and other work accidents – or through chemical exposure to asbestos, benzene or other toxic products Continuing to Build on Our Reputation for Excellence Provost Umphrey’s attorneys, paralegals and support staff continue to demonstrate the essential legal expertise and tenacity necessary to successfully advocate, negotiate and litigate for the best interests of Americans against even the most powerful industries. At Provost Umphrey, all of our equity partners and many of our member and associate attorneys are Board Certified in Personal Injury Trial Law by the Texas Board of Legal Specialization. We bring together high-stakes case experience, strong connections to expert resources, and leading-edge technology to deliver top-quality legal research and presentations in the courtroom. Our integrity and determination to see justice done shines through in our union commitment and work in the community as well as our advocacy for valued clients. From offices in Beaumont and Houston, Texas and Nashville, Tennessee we handle cases across the United States. Request a free case evaluation today.

Full Description: AOG Accessories specialize in providing repair services covering equipment manufactured by many of the galley equipment and interior parts for major OEM’s. Our goal revolves in delivering a quality and reliable product with every repair to help reduce overall cost. We specialize, and have a focused approach to what parts we support; our experienced and well trained specialists repair these components to provide proficient, effective and dependable fault finding and modification. When combined with a modern, well equipped facility and a large and continuous investment in spare parts to ensure we have the right parts in stock that our customers can be sure of receiving the very best level of service and support. With so many options available to operators when specifying galley equipment it often means even a small size fleet will have galley equipment such as ovens and coffee makers with multiple part numbers from many different manufacturers. With AOG’s varied capability list of hundreds of part numbers we can offer our customers a one stop solution thus allowing customers to deal with a single repair coordinator able to assist with repairs, spares and exchanges across all part numbers and manufacturers. In addition, we offer flexible support solutions to meet customers’ needs including time and materials fixed pricing, flat exchange program and will always accommodate and tailor repair programs to meet our customer’s requirement.
